        "\n",
        "## Phase 1: SIGReg + Bidirectional Architecture\n",
        "\n",
        "### Architecture Changes\n",
        "\n",
        "The V15 architecture makes three key changes from V2:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. **Bidirectional context encoder** (vs causal in V2): At inference, the full past is available. Causal masking was unnecessarily restrictive.\n",
        "\n",
        "2. **Full-sequence target** (x_{0:t+k} vs x_{t+1:t+k}): The target encoder sees the complete trajectory. V14 showed -2.1 RMSE improvement frozen.\n",
        "\n",
        "3. **Shared encoder weights**: Context and target use the same transformer (no EMA for SIGReg config, or EMA of same encoder for EMA config). This halves parameters.\n",
        "\n",
        "**New in V15**: Proper Epps-Pulley SIGReg (EP characteristic function test, not moment matching). Fully vectorized across all M=512 projections simultaneously.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Experiment A: EP-SIGReg Isotropy"
      ],
      "id": "bd81a75c"
    },
